Package: rikus-zram
Version: 1.18
Architecture: all
Maintainer: Gilbert Rikus <gilbert@rikus.info>
Section: utils
Priority: optional
Depends: python3, python3-gi, gir1.2-gtk-3.0, polkitd | policykit-1, pkexec | policykit-1, zram-tools, procps, init-system-helpers, apt, mount, btrfs-progs
Homepage: https://github.com/Zahnschmerz/rikus-zram
Description: Set up zram, swappiness and swap files without a terminal
 Rikus Zram turns Linux memory tuning into a window with sliders. It shows
 what is currently running, recommends what fits this particular machine,
 and applies changes only after you confirm them.
 .
 zram compresses rarely used data inside RAM instead of paging it out to a
 slow disk - typically 3-4 times smaller. Configuring it normally means
 typing commands and editing system files.
 .
 Unlike other tools, it can also set zram up on a machine that has none yet:
 it installs the package, writes the settings, and switches the service on -
 including a start script on systems without systemd, where zram-tools ships
 only a systemd unit.
 .
 Features: live view of RAM, zram and swap with a plain-language verdict;
 recommendations calculated from RAM size, disk type, filesystem and
 hibernation setup; three sliders for zram size, swappiness and swap file;
 a preview before any change; a backup of every file touched; verification
 that the change took effect; and an undo button.
 .
 Works with systemd and with SysVinit, so also on MX Linux and antiX. On
 btrfs the swap file is placed in its own subvolume so Timeshift can still
 take snapshots. Swap partitions are never modified.
 .
 User interface in German or English, chosen automatically.
